----------------------------------------
steps to deploy this on aws ec2 instance
----------------------------------------
step 1 : create a ubuntu instance. use 4GB ram
			- add security inbound rules : HTTP,HTTPS,Custom(8080) for both IPv4 and IPv6(to access in mobile)
			- and also 3306 for MYSQL
			
step 2 : install java in it.
			sudo apt update
			sudo apt install openjdk-17-jdk -y
			java -version
			
step 3 : install mysql server
			sudo apt install mysql-server -y
			sudo mysql_secure_installation
			
			#Create DB + User:
			sudo mysql -u root -p
				
			#create a database and a user and grant privilages	
			CREATE DATABASE appdb;
			CREATE USER 'appuser'@'%' IDENTIFIED BY 'StrongPassword';
			GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON appdb.* TO 'appuser'@'%';
			FLUSH PRIVILEGES;
			
			===================================================================
			Error Case
			===================================================================
			1. Check if MySQL is running
				sudo systemctl status mysql

				#If not running:
				sudo systemctl start mysql

			2️. Check if MySQL is listening on port 3306
				sudo lsof -i:3306

				#If nothing prints → MySQL is NOT running or not bound to correct IP.

			3️. Fix bind-address
			#Edit MySQL config:
				sudo nano /etc/mysql/mysql.conf.d/mysqld.cnf

			#Find:
				bind-address = 127.0.0.1

			#Change to:
				bind-address = 0.0.0.0

			#Restart:
				sudo systemctl restart mysql

			4️. Create user for remote login
			#Login:
				sudo mysql -u root -p

			#Run:
				CREATE USER 'appuser'@'%' IDENTIFIED BY 'Password123';
				GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON *.* TO 'appuser'@'%';
				FLUSH PRIVILEGES;

			5️. Test MySQL locally
				mysql -u appuser -p -h localhost
			========================================================================
							
step 4 : configure application.properties(recommended create database with same name locally also)
			spring.datasource.url=jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/appdb
			spring.datasource.username=appuser
			spring.datasource.password=StrongPassword
			spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=update
			spring.jpa.show-sql=true
			server.port=8080
			
step 5 : do maven install and get the jar file of the project and upload it the ec2 using command or MobaXterm
			
step 5 : Create a Systemd Service (Auto-Start)
			sudo nano /etc/systemd/system/app.service
			
			#copy paste the following instructions
			[Unit]
			Description=Expense Tracker Spring Boot App
			After=network.target

			[Service]
			User=ubuntu
			WorkingDirectory=/home/ubuntu
			ExecStart=/usr/bin/java -jar /home/ubuntu/app.jar
			SuccessExitStatus=143
			Restart=always
			RestartSec=3

			[Install]
			WantedBy=multi-user.target
			
			#Save & exit.
			#Reload:
				sudo systemctl daemon-reload

			#Start:
				sudo systemctl start expense

			#Enable auto-start on reboot:
				sudo systemctl enable expense

			#Check status:
				sudo systemctl status expense

step 6 : to check the logs of the app
			cat app.log
			tail -50 app.log
			
step 7 : Access application at
			http://<your-ec2-ip>:8080			